txt.en: 'Yes, I agree. The main gate will be the most reliable way inside Goblin-town, but we will need a distraction.\n\n'I think it is now my turn to accompany you on this mission, my friend. I will make certain you are able to get inside the main gate, if you promise to find our missing Baggins!'

'I have heard that there are numerous back entrances to Goblin-town, but they are unreliable and difficult to find. By the time we found one, if we could even get it open, it might be too late for poor Bilbo! We need to think of some other way to get inside. Do you have any ideas, [placeholder]?'
07. The Further Adventures of Bilbo Baggins, Chapter 7
You must find a way to breach a barrier to reach your mission objective.
Bilbo Baggins has run afoul of the goblins of the Misty Mountains... again!
Complete 'Mission: The Further Adventures of Bilbo Baggins, Chapter 7'
Your mission is to free Bilbo Baggins from the goblins. Speak to Celeblír to set forth!
Celeblír is west of the Last Homely House, near the Town Crier.
'The depths of Goblin-town are sure to be dangerous, but you will need to search them if you are to rescue Bilbo!'
